## Key design decisions made in Phase 4

1. **Reuse the LLM accessor pattern.**
   `Kernel::register_knowledge()` and
   `Kernel::knowledge(key)` are
   structurally identical to the LLM
   version. The only delta: the
   underlying `CapabilityRegistry` method
   is also `register_knowledge` (per the
   Phase 0 spec; the `Kernel` is a thin
   facade that delegates).
2. **No new error variants.** Phase 4
   uses the existing `KernelError` enum
   (`NoKnowledgeAdapter` if the
   capability was never registered,
   `UnknownKnowledgeKey` if the key is
   unknown). Both are symmetric to the
   LLM-side errors.
3. **Real-impl conformance test, not a
   phase-4-only test file.** The IMPL
   allowed "or extend the existing
   `knowledge_v1.rs`" — we extended.
   The new test is
   `knowledge_v1_conformance_suite_against_json_adapter`,
   co-located with the existing
   `MockAdapter` test. Future sibling
   adapters (Postgres, Neo4j) follow
   the same pattern: extend
   `knowledge_v1.rs` with a
   `*_against_<backend>` test that runs
   the same `run_conformance_suite`.
4. **Re-`cargo fmt` was not needed.**
   The new code was formatted correctly
   on first write (the new tests in
   `knowledge_integration.rs` and
   `knowledge_v1.rs` were inspected
   line-by-line for line length and
   brace style). `cargo fmt --all
   -- --check` is the
   `Makefile`-driven gate, and it passed
   first try.
5. **`cargo doc` was not regressed.**
   The new `docs/plugins/KnowledgeJson.md`
   is plain Markdown (not a doc comment
   in the crate), so it doesn't affect
   `cargo doc`. The crate doc-comments
   were not touched in this phase.

## Open questions for the next session

1. **Knowledge engines in the HTTP layer.**
   When the v1.5 HTTP layer lands (the
   next major work in
   `docs/roadmap/v1.5.md`), the
   `GET /knowledge/topics` + `POST
   /knowledge/store` handlers are the
   first consumers of
   `Kernel::knowledge(key)`. The pattern
   is identical to the LLM handlers
   that already exist. No design work
   needed — just a "wire it up" task.
2. **Knowledge engines in `afa-cli`.**
   The v1.5 `afa-cli` gains
   `afa knowledge list-topics` and
   `afa knowledge search` subcommands.
   Same pattern as the LLM subcommands.
   The `Kernel::knowledge(key)` accessor
   is the entry point. No design work
   needed.
3. **Metadata sidecar for lossless
   recovery.** Phase 3's documented v1
   limitation (the topic name can't be
   perfectly recovered from the slug
   alone) is still open. A future pack
   adds `<record_id>.json` next to each
   `<record_id>.md`. The IMPL has this
   in the "Deferred Items" section of
   the TRD.
4. **`search_throughput` benchmark.**
   Deferred from Phase 4. v1 ships
   correctness, not throughput numbers.
   The benchmark is a future pack's
   problem (probably the same pack that
   adds the v1.5 search relevance
   improvements).

